case class Sensor(resid: String, date: String, time: String, hz: Double, disp: Double, flo: Double, sedPPM: Double, psi: Double, chlPPM: Double) extends Serializable 
val timeout = 10 // Terminate after N seconds
val batchSeconds = 2 // Size of batch intervals

val topics: String = "/user/mapr/pump:sensor"
System.out.println("Subscribed to : " + topics)

val brokers = "maprdemo:9092" // not needed for MapR Streams, needed for Kafka
val groupId = "sparkApplication"
val pollTimeout = "5000"
val ssc = new StreamingContext(sc, Seconds(2))

val topicsSet = topics.split(",").toSet
val kafkaParams = Map[String, String](
      ConsumerConfig.BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS_CONFIG -> brokers,
      ConsumerConfig.GROUP_ID_CONFIG -> groupId,
      ConsumerConfig.KEY_DESERIALIZER_CLASS_CONFIG ->
        "org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer",
      ConsumerConfig.AUTO_OFFSET_RESET_CONFIG -> "earliest",
      ConsumerConfig.VALUE_DESERIALIZER_CLASS_CONFIG ->
        "org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer",
      ConsumerConfig.ENABLE_AUTO_COMMIT_CONFIG -> "true",
      "spark.kafka.poll.time" -> pollTimeout,
      "spark.streaming.kafka.consumer.poll.ms" -> "8192"
)

paragraphs.text:
val linesDStream = KafkaUtils.createDirectStream[String, String](ssc, kafkaParams, topicsSet)

val  sensorDStream = linesDStream.map(_._2).map(_.split(",")).map(p =>  
      Sensor(p(0), p(1), p(2), p(3).toDouble, p(4).toDouble, p(5).toDouble, p(6).toDouble, p(7).toDouble, p(8).toDouble))

sensorDStream.foreachRDD { rdd =>

      // There exists at least one element in RDD
      if (!rdd.isEmpty) {
        println("sensor data")
        val df = rdd.toDF()
         df.show()
        df.registerTempTable("sensor")

      }
    }
ssc.remember(Minutes(2)) 

ssc.start() 
ssc.awaitTerminationOrTimeout(1 * 5 * 1000)

%sql
SELECT resid,date, time, min( psi) as minpsi  FROM sensor GROUP BY resid, date, time order by minpsi

%sql
SELECT resid,date, time,  MAX(psi) as maxpsi, min(psi) as minpsi, avg(psi) as avgpsi  FROM sensor GROUP BY resid,date, time

%sql
SELECT resid, date, psi, count(resid) as count FROM sensor where psi < '100' GROUP BY resid,date, psi

%sql
SELECT resid,date, min( psi) as minpsi  FROM sensor GROUP BY resid, date order by minpsi

%sql
SELECT resid,date, time, avg( psi) as avgpsi  FROM sensor GROUP BY resid, date, time order by date, time
